text: {| |} ''''' was launched in 1826 at St Martin's, New Brunswick. She entered Lloyd's Register in 1827 with M. Tait, master, and W. Andrew, owner.Supple. pages "S", Seq.№S21. She then proceeded to sail between England and Canada. However, she was on a voyage from Mauritius to Glasgow, Renfrewshire, when she was driven ashore in Table Bay on 1 September 1830 and was wrecked. ==Citations and references== Citations References * Category:1826 ships Category:Age of Sail merchant ships of England Category:Maritime incidents in September 1830
